replyContent: Dear XhaoticHeaven. There's contact info in the app (Main Menu / HELP / Contact developer), in the play store listing, and at the website. Furthermore, to record an own sample, long press RECORD, then choose "Capture Sample from Microphone" from the menu.

content: Just when I thought nothing could top the original G-Stomper, this new synth version comes along and totally amazes me.  Using the combination of both applications means I have an incredible set of tools in my arsenal to create some insane, killer sounding music.  I'll buy anything from this developer, without question or hesitation.  Thanks for building another top-tier music production app.

This is by far the most comprehensive music application on the market.The third 'hidden' oscillator really adds an industrial element to the mix.The arpeggiator is neat and simple to use and encompass 4 octaves!  My one question~How does one go about placing longer notes on the pattern grid?
replyContent: Thanks a lot for your feedback Martin. About your question: I wrote a short "howto" in the Tips and Tricks section of the support forum. Guess this will answer the question: http://www.planet-h.com/gstomperbb/viewtopic.php?f=15&t=228 . If you have any further questions, feel free to ask either in the forum or mail us to gstomper@planet-h.com

replyContent: Hey Joe, thanks for your feedback. This is a known google play issue and has nothing to do with g-stomper. Please follow the steps at the FAQ : http://www.planet-h.com/gstomper/gstfaq.html to fix the problem. If you still get the message, contact us at gstomper@planet-h.com and we help you sorting it out.

content: Multi synth sequencer. Export audio with bpm auto named at end! Default bpm. If u love audio sequencing and synths, this is a must buy!
MORE SAMPLE SOUNDS IS WHATS NEEDED
replyContent: Thanks a lot for your feedback Roland. There'll be more add-ons for sure. The VA-Beast is still new, and add-ons will get built soon. The next update will bring sequencing functionality in form of a polyphonic step sequencer. Furthermore the synth gets multitimbral, then you can use up to 12 concurrent synths at once.

replyContent: Thanks a lot for your feedback, Stephane. There'll be a G-Stomper Beat Studio integrated version for sure;), the integration is already on progress;), e.t.a. around end of February. Once the mobile DAW is complete, I'll definitely think about a pc version, vst interface, etc.
